The following packages were derived from or inspired by the original Shelob project:
  auth/        — cookie-based login and token extraction
  openapi/     — OpenAPI spec loading and router construction
  request/     — HTTP request assembly from spec parameters
  bodyParams/  — request body generation
  generateInput/ — random data generation per schema type
  security/    — security header helpers
  urlParams/   — path, query, header, cookie parameter handling
  response/    — response validation (legacy path)
  logging/     — JSON crash/test log files

The following packages are new in shelob-ng and were not part of the original Shelob:
  corpus/      — AFL-style weighted corpus with persistence and dynamic value pool
  mutator/     — structural, byte-level, and security payload mutation strategies
  coverage/    — Coverage Sidecar Protocol (CSP) client and no-op stub
  checkers/    — modular security checkers (BehavioralPatterns, UseAfterFree,
                 InvalidDynamicObject, LeakageRule, NameSpaceRule, SchemaViolation)
  sequence/    — stateful CRUD sequence builder, runner, and replay persistence
  apicov/      — per-operation API spec coverage tracker
  ui/          — libfuzzer-style terminal display (INITED/NEW/pulse/FINDING/DONE)
  run/         — coverage-guided main fuzzing loop (fully rewritten)
  adapters/    — CSP adapter reference implementations (Node.js, Go, Python, C)
  example/     — OWASP Juice Shop walkthrough (10 scenarios, Makefile, docker-compose)
